    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-11-05T08:35:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-11-05T08:35:00-05:00" n="505"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d505">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">761.91/11–544: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Iran</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Morris</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tehran</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-11-05T17:00:00+03:25"
                            >November 5, 1944—5 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received November 6—12:53 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>819. During conversation with Soviet Ambassador Maximov on November 3 British
                    Ambassador expressed hope differences between Soviet Embassy and Iranian
                    Government over oil concession would be <pb facs="0482" n="470" xml:id="pg_470"
                    /> adjusted. Maximov seemed to have great difficulty controlling himself and
                    replied that there had never been any dispute over oil concession, that
                    difficulty was solely with Saed personally. From this and reports received
                    through sources close to Soviet Embassy Bullard thinks Russians have decided to
                    take line that Saed is personally unfriendly to USSR and tinged with fascism and
                    that this rather than refusal of concession is cause of their
                    dissatisfaction.</p>
                <p>Sent to Department, repeated to Moscow.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Morris</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
